  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH and Nutrition Interventions for drought affected areas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Receiving a total of US$ 2.8 million, UNICEF will use $1 million to conduct water trucking for 30 days to reach 50,000 drought-affected people with safe water. 6,000 hygiene kits as well as WASH messages will be distributed to support the same 50,000 people. The remaining $1.8 million will be used by UNICEF to screen 242,000 girls and boys for malnutrition and treat 11,000 girls and boys with severe acute malnutrition with ready-to-use therapeutic food (RUTF). In addition, 53,000 pregnant and lactating women and 500 male caregivers will receive counselling on infant and young child feeding (IYCF) practices. 295,000 drought-affected Somalis, including 53,000 women and 123,420 girls, will be reached by the nutrition component of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
